      "stem_html": "<p>Name the following amine, including <i>R</i>,<i>S</i> stereochemistry, and draw the product of its reaction with excess iodomethane followed by heating with Ag<sub>2</sub>O (Hofmann elimination). Is the stereochemistry of the alkene product <i>Z</i> or <i>E</i>? Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaFVaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--15cd99e5ddea96f5f1107130ab2166bab02aa49c/OChem_24_EC_016.jpg\" alt=\"A ball-and-stick model of a three-carbon chain with benzene rings on C 1 and C 2, and an N H 2 group on C 1.\">",
